secondaryOutcomes.description:
The SF-36 has eight scaled scores; the scores are weighted sums of the questions in each section. Scores range from 0 - 100 Lower scores = more disability, higher scores = less disability. The 8 subscales or domains are as follows:

Physical functioning (10 items);

Role limitations due to physical health (4 items); Role limitations due to emotional problems (4 items); Energy/fatigue (4 items); Emotional well-being (5 items); Social functioning (2 items); Pain (2 items); General health (5 items).
